'''Ophelia Piner''' (October 22, 2052 - December 2, 2151) was an American professional basketball player in the WNBA. 

==Early life and education==
Piner was born in Houston, Texas to Diana (2017 - 2091) and Cooper Piner (2018 - 2103). Her mother was a school administrator, and her father was a marine biologist. She had an older brother, Steven (2039 - 2115), a grocer for Henderson Foods, and a Cavalier King Charles spaniel named Lanika (d. 2065). 

